The paper deals with community detection in networks, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which specifically deals with the analysis of social and information networks. The paper also discusses the use of algorithms for community detection, which falls under cs.SD (Software Development and Programming), as well as cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks), which deals with the study of social and economic systems as networks. The paper also presents a new algorithm for community detection, which involves data analysis and machine learning, and thus could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
